<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 92-16-06 - Freon Compressor Drive Belt Replacement</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi921606" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>92-16-06</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>June, 1992</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>CAB</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Freon Compressor Drive Belt Replacement</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>York</vendor>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to all 1991 models with L10 and 3176 engines and Standard (York) freon
                    compressors.
                </para>
                <para>Freon compressor drive belts that have been used in production since approximately January 1,
                    1991, are not constructed correctly and may flip off. Belts constructed especially to drive freon
                    compressors have been released in service parts for all 1991 models with an L10 or 3176 engine and a
                    standard (York) compressor.
                </para>
                <para>When replacing the belt, the belt tension should be set at 130 lbs.
                    <emph type="bold">COLD</emph>. The use of a belt tension gauge is mandatory. After 15 to 30 minutes
                    run-in, check belt tension. The belt tension should remain at 100 lbs. or greater. Retension if
                    necessary. After 1000 miles, recheck and adjust the belt tension. The vehicle should then operate to
                    normal maintenance intervals for belt check and tension. Any misalignment should be corrected at the
                    time of belt installation.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
